                Carviliae <expan><abbr>P</abbr><ex>ubli</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>iliae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Censonill</abbr><ex>ae</ex></expan> Magni <lb n="2"/>Rufi <expan><abbr>proc</abbr><ex>uratoris</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> XX <expan><abbr>her</abbr><ex>editatium</ex></expan> per <expan><abbr>Hisp</abbr><ex>aniam</ex></expan> <lb n="3"/><expan><abbr>Baet</abbr><ex>icam</ex></expan> et <expan><abbr>Lusitan</abbr><ex>iam</ex></expan> item <expan><abbr>proc</abbr><ex>uratoris</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> <lb n="4"/>per <expan><abbr>Baet</abbr><ex>icam</ex></expan> ad <expan><abbr>kal</abbr><ex>endarium</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Vegetian</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan> item <expan><abbr>pr<supplied reason="lost">o</supplied>c</abbr><ex>uratoris</ex></expan> <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>Aug</abbr><ex>usti</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>prov</abbr><ex>inciae</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Baet</abbr><ex>icae</ex></expan> ad <expan><abbr>ducen</abbr><ex>a</ex></expan> Ac<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>il</abbr><ex>ia</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>Plec</abbr><ex>usa</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="6"/>amicae op<supplied reason="lost">timae <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>ono</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>at</ex></expan></supplied>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Zur Karriere des Magnius Rufus vgl. H.-G. Pflaum, Les carrières procuratoriennes 2 (Paris 1960) 633, Nr. 236. - Acilia Plecusa durch weitere Inschriften aus Singilia bekannt (CIL II 2016-2020), vgl. besonders CIL II² 5, 780 = CIL II 2029 = ILS 1405 (Ehrung des Magnius Rufus durch Acilia Plecusa). Datierung: Prokuraturen fallen in die Zeit d. Commodus bzw. Septimius Severus vor 198 n. Chr. (B): AE 1978: Z. 4: kal(endarium) / Vegetianu(m); Sillierès, AE 1978: AE 1978: Z. 4: proc(uratoris); Z. 5: A[cil(ia)]; Z. 6: o[ptimae ---].</p>
            </div>
